Chief Minister N. Chandrababu Naidu has instructed all District Collectors and Nodal Officers in the State to formulate plans for digging one farm pond in every five acres of land across the State.During a teleconference from Pathikonda in Kurnool district on Thursday , Mr. Naidu said that he had launched the Panta Sanjeevani scheme at Pathikonda which envisaged digging one lakh farm ponds in every district in the State. Most representations received in Janmabhoomi - Maa Vooru programme pertaining to ration cards, pensions, pending housing bills, drinking water scarcity and individual latrines, Mr. Naidu said and instructed officials to dispose off the petitions expeditiously.Take up works for development of villages without delay, he said. Villages would be classified basing on 20 indicators and development undertaken to change the peopleâ€™s lifestyles, the Chief Minister said. He directed to conduct rangoli and cookery competitions for women during the Janmabhoomi programme.Meanwhile, Kurnool administration prepared a booklet on Janmabhoomi programme.Tthe issues to be taken up in gram sabhas and the booklets should be prepared district-wise, Mr. Naidu told the Collectors.Collectors told to formulate plans for digging up one farm pond in every five acres of land